    "settings": [{"type":"paragraph","content":"Section design by GemPages. [Click here to start design](https://admin.shopify.com/store/7tukht-p1/apps/gempages-cro/app/shopify/edit?pageType=GP_STATIC&editorId=612947697678156512&sectionId=612947720209957600)"},{"type":"select","label":"Section Preload","id":"section_preload","options":[{"label":"On","value":"true"},{"label":"Off","value":"false"},{"label":"Off Lazy Script","value":"off_lazy_script"}],"default":"false"},{"type":"text","label":"Checksum","id":"checksum"},{"type":"html","id":"gghLPyCk2qj_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"gghLPyCk2qj_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/Rectangle_41021.png"},{"type":"html","id":"ggNSNHojJ3l_text","label":"ggNSNHojJ3l_text","default":"Your Boots Are Destroying Your Feet Before the Concrete Even Gets a Chance"},{"type":"html","id":"gglhiZ70pao_text","label":"gglhiZ70pao_text","default":"<p>Most workers blame the concrete. Hard floors. Long hours standing. And yes, all of that plays a part.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>But the boot itself is making it significantly worse.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Traditional safety boots are built around a rigid last and thick leather upper. That rigidity means the boot doesn't flex with your foot. It forces your foot to adapt to the shoe rather than the other way around. Over an eight hour shift, that constant resistance causes friction at the heel and toe box. That's where the blisters come from. That's why your ankles feel locked up by the afternoon.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The stiffness isn't a sign of quality. It's what happens when a boot is designed around a safety standard rather than around a human foot.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>A boot that weighs 460 grams and flexes like a trainer doesn't just reduce fatigue from the weight. It stops fighting your foot all day long. The blisters ease. The ankle stiffness goes. The feet that were done by lunchtime start making it to the end of the shift in one piece.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The concrete isn't going anywhere. But what you put on your feet before you step onto it is entirely your choice.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggbH4SmoZ3v_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggbH4SmoZ3v_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0673/2562/4490/files/Rectangle_41021.png"}],
    "blocks": [{"type": "@app"}],
